details.description: Night Swim Coffee was born in Charlotte, North Carolina as the centerpiece of a unified venture for Not Just Coffee and Undercurrent Coffee to create a specialty coffee roaster in Charlotte. In our cafes, Night Swim Coffee offers the same thoughtfully prepared food and beverages, attention to detail, and hospitable atmosphere that is enjoyed in the legacy Not Just Coffee and Undercurrent Coffee cafes, but in a setting designed in a collaborative effort across the team to create a unique experience at every location.

reviews_data.review_text: It's 3:30p and they're out of everything I wanted to order, improve supply and inventory management.
Coffee isn’t horrible but the guy in the glasses with the little man bun needs to check his attitude.
Great baristas that know coffee. Excellent cortado and breakfast sandwiches.
Great spot to grab coffee while staying down the street for a conference, almost no crowds since it is tucked into an office building.
This is the place in town to drink a fine coffee. Night Swim roasts many unique high quality beans, and the place is quite interesting. Highly recommended stop in town.
One of the best matchas I’ve tried! They make their own vanilla syrup with brown and it’s to die for. Service is always great and convenient location as I work on the next door building!
Great coffee, nice vibe!
Beautiful space, great service and very good coffee.
Located in the BoA building, my favorite cold brew in Charlotte. Always recommended.
Best coffee in downtown Charlotte - hands down. Don’t let the location in a corporate building dissuade you from checking it out. Great place to meet for a casual work meeting or answer a few emails.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Avocado Toast Vegan GF Option Available

reviews_data.review_text: I got ice caramel latte and  it was so good. The service is great, all the baristas are so friendly
Really great employees, clean space, very nice meeting space, great coffee.

We were here from out of town to host an event close by and stumbled upon this place. Great food and coffee, exceptional customer service. There is such a great vibe here. For community groups, there is even an awesome closed door space which we used for a team meeting. Call in advance to reserve. Will come here any time we are in Charlotte!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Avocado Toast Vegan GF Option Available, Alt Milk Options, Espresso 2oz

reviews_data.review_text: The staff at this location is phenomenal, very accommodating, kind, and helpful. So glad we found this spot!

Great coffee! Excellent service!

Mighty Swim Coffee is my absolute favorite coffee spot. I simply adore the minimalist and corporate barista environment, which perfectly combines with the cozy atmosphere of a small coffee shop. It's truly the best of both worlds. The coffee here is bold, yet not overpowering, and every drink is meticulously crafted to perfection. I can't help but eagerly anticipate each visit to this wonderful establishment.
Had a fantastic cappuccino here today. Cool modern space also.
The focaccia sandwich here is ridiculous. So good. I get it at least once a week.

Everything is near perfection - coffee, seatings, baristas - except for the young kid who seems to close out the shop, throwing out stuff, handling items carelessly, making unnecessary, disturbing noises while dozens of customers are still around.
Great latte and grits!

Cool little spot to grab a drink and do a little bit to work or have a small meeting. Multiple seating options and lots of glass wall to make the place feel bigger. The staff was friendly and helpful. The drinks taste good as well. Getting a cold brew and choosing more than one flavor option like vanilla and caramel was a great choice. They also have a water stand which is nice for a quick hydration in between work. They also have WiFi if that wasn’t obvious by this point.

This place smells so good when you walk in. I had the caramel latte and it was one of the best I've ever had, I needed to leave a review. I love that they make their own real sauce and it's not a thin syrup flavor. 10 out of 10 can't wait to be back in town so I can return.
Delicious coffee spot inside the Bank of America building. They have breakfast and lunch sandwiches, wraps etc. There is a good selection  of coffee and tea too.
Love this coffee shop. Good flavor, high quality ingredients such as milk alternatives

Pretentiousness not justified by coffee quality.  Coffee quality is mediocre at best and baristas are not friendly and are unhelpful.  Drinks only come in one size and baristas are completely inflexible in offering other sizes.  Coffee needs to be much better  for this level of snottery.
Love the overnight oats!!  Coffee is great too.
Great coffee with a couple of excellent sandwich options. It doesn’t get a big lunch crowd so there are usually plenty of open tables.
Came here every day while visiting Charlotte.  Cool coffee shop with good vibes.  For any others having trouble finding it, its in the Bank of America building on the first floor
Great vanilla latte

This is a hidden gem that needs attention! We got caramel iced lattes, and they were amazing. The coffee was top notch and the ingredients were high quality. The staff were amazing! They were especially helpful and cheerful. They provided excellent service. If you're walking around uptown and need a boost, stop in and give it a try.
Best pour over I've had in a while

Yummy breakfast sandwich.
Nice ambiance and music.
Coffee very good,  staff friendly.

This is a hidden gem on South Tryon! My go to is their batch brew coffee with no cream or sugar. It’s very rich, strong, and not overly fruity. I also love the energy in there! It very bright, modern, and happy!
Delicious must try and they nail their coffee roast!!
A bit pricey but great spot. Great beans. Good latte art. Really enjoyed my flat white

What a neat shop tucked away on the first floor of the Bank of America building. Colleen was amazing to talk to! She took the time to talk with me about some of her favorite roasts and tea blends. Everything was delicious & so fitting with the inviting environment of the shop! I'm excited to go back and try more 🙂

Probably my favorite of the new locations, it’s a truly gorgeous space, kinda like a museum with comfy couches. And the coffee is as good as it gets, combining Not Just Coffee and Undercurrent Coffee’s talent and experience, while also roasting the beans themselves. Love how everybody in the Charlotte coffee scene is friends with each other!!

Turns out the name Night Swim is meant to conjure nostalgic images of our youth, when we would float around carefree under the comforting caress of the moon.
Wonderful shop design with fantastic coffee. Take a step out of your day into the aesthetically pleasing lobby coffee shop and entice your senses with a wonderful latte or cortado. Tons of choices.

Underwhelming. Got the Masala Chai thinking it was going to be made with a fresh homemade masala mix. Sadly, it taste like the boxed chai that chain shops offer. Too sweet and no Masala flavor. Definitely will not be going back. It’s priced like a specialty coffee shop with a mediocre product. I do like the interior though.
